<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-09-19T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-09-19T01:00:00-05:00" n="605" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d605">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">822.01/9–1947: Circular telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Representatives
                                    in the American Republics</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-09-19T02:00:00-04:00">September
                                    19, 1947—2 a.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Please inform Govt to which you are accredited that US Govt is
                            instructing US <gloss target="#t_Amb1">Amb</gloss> at Quito to enter
                            into normal relations with new Govt of Ecuador on Monday, Sept 22.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>